## Conclusion: A Site Waiting to Be Rediscovered

Goan Bogame is more than a collection of ruins—it is a puzzle, a challenge to historians, archaeologists, and storytellers alike. Its silent stones hold the potential to reshape our understanding of pre-colonial Somali civilization, trade networks, and urban development. Yet, until more comprehensive studies are conducted, it remains a shadow of its former self—a city that once was, now waiting for the world to remember.

For now, it stands as a reminder: beneath the sands of time, there are always more stories to uncover.